Package: sussexthesis
Title: An updated Sussex R Markdown thesis template using the bookdown package
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chester", "Ismay", email = "chester.ismay@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Danielle", "Evans", email = "danielle.evans@sussex.ac.uk", role = "cre"))
Description: sussexthesis uses the bookdown package and LaTeX and Word thesis templates from
    Reed College to create a thesis consistent with the requirements of the University of Sussex. This package aims to encourage reproducible research using
    simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to produce plots
    and analyses as well.
Maintainer: Danielle Evans <danielle.evans@sussex.ac.uk>
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    bookdown,
    knitr,
    here,
    R.utils
Suggests:
    remotes,
    usethis
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: pandoc (>= 1.18) - https://pandoc.org
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
